commit f6245070ad77622a2450f514074fa09fdcd78cb1
Author: René J.V. Bertin <rjvbertin@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Feb 21 00:22:16 2026 +0100

    Not all I/O engines support testing with multiple queues
    
    and fio will issue a note about how it capped the requested number
    of queues to 1 when a synchronous engine is used. This commit
    
    * handles the presence of such a note via the statusbar
    * implements and invokes a function to do the capping before fio
      is called, in a similarly runtime fashion and for the engines
      known to be involved (currently only "fio-default", aka "psync")
      The UI is updated too (button texts).
    
    Committed from host : Portia.local

